# perfinfo PMDA help file in the ASCII format
#
# lines beginning with a # are ignored
# lines beginning @ introduce a new entry of the form
#  @ metric_name oneline_text
#  help test goes
#  here over multiple lines
#  ...
#
# the metric_name is decoded against the default PMNS -- as a special case,
# a name of the form NNN.MM (for numeric NNN and MM) is interpreted as an
# instance domain identification, and the text describes the instance domain
#
# blank lines before the @ line are ignored
#
@ kvmstat.efer_reload Number of Extended Feature Enable Register (EFER) reloads.
@ kvmstat.exits Number of guest exits from I/O port accesses. 
@ kvmstat.fpu_reload Number of reload fpu(Float Point Unit).
@ kvmstat.halt_attempted_poll Number of times the vcpu attempts to polls.
@ kvmstat.halt_exits  Number of guest exits due to halt calls. This type of exit is usually seen when a guest is idle.
@ kvmstat.halt_successful_poll The number of times the vcpu attempts to polls successfully.
@ kvmstat.halt_wakeup  Number of wakeups from a halt.
@ kvmstat.host_state_reload Number of full reloads of the host state (currently tallies MSR setup and guest MSR reads).
@ kvmstat.hypercalls Number of guest hypervisor service calls.
@ kvmstat.insn_emulation Number of insn_emulation attempts.
@ kvmstat.insn_emulation_fail Number of failed insn_emulation attempts.
@ kvmstat.invlpg Number of invlpg attepts. 
@ kvmstat.io_exits Number of guest exits from I/O port accesses.
@ kvmstat.irq_exits Number of guest exits due to external interrupts.
@ kvmstat.irq_injections Number of interrupts sent to guests.
@ kvmstat.irq_window Number of guest exits from an outstanding interrupt window.
@ kvmstat.largepages Number of large pages currently in use.
@ kvmstat.mmio_exits Number of guest exits due to memory mapped I/O (MMIO) accesses.
@ kvmstat.mmu_cache_miss Number of cache miss.
@ kvmstat.mmu_flooded Detection count of excessive write operations to an MMU page. This counts detected write operations not of individual write operations.
@ kvmstat.mmu_pde_zapped Number of page directory entry (PDE) destruction operations.
@ kvmstat.mmu_pte_updated Number of PTE updated. 
@ kvmstat.mmu_pte_write Number of PTE write.
@ kvmstat.mmu_recycled Number of shadow pages that can be reclaimed.
@ kvmstat.mmu_shadow_zapped Number of shadow pages that has been zapped.
@ kvmstat.mmu_unsync Number of non-synchronized pages which are not yet unlinked 
@ kvmstat.nmi_injections Number of Non-maskable Interrupt (NMI) injections.
@ kvmstat.nmi_window Number of guest exits from (outstanding) Non-maskable Interrupt (NMI) windows.
@ kvmstat.pf_fixed Number of fixed (non-paging) page table entry (PTE) maps.
@ kvmstat.pf_guest Number of page faults injected into guests.
@ kvmstat.remote_tlb_flush Number of tlb_flush operations performed by the hypervisor.
@ kvmstat.request_irq Number of guest interrupt window request exits.
@ kvmstat.signal_exits Number of guest exits due to pending signals from the host.
@ kvmstat.tlb_flush Number of tlb_flush operations performed by the hypervisor.
